                                        Wed May 11 11:56:46 JST 1994
                                                                SONY

Dear Bitstream Exchange AHG members,

This bitstream is created for the Video Conformance Testing AHG
for the test of 
"Alternating top/bottom, ZZ/Alternative, Intra/Non-intra 
 tables in I pictures" .

Parameters of the bitstream"sony-ct1" are the following:


Bitstream ID:  6.
Description:   Alternating top/bottom, ZZ/Alternative, Intra/Non-intra VLC 
               tables in I pictures
	       (+ Linear/Non_linear Q, 
	          Conceal_MV on/off, 
	          Intra_dc 8/9/10bit precision)
Stresses:      parser
Justification: Sloppy decoders may not handle all scenarios.
Organizations: Sony
Parameters:     
	
	--- sony-ct1 ---
        Bitstream file          sony-ct1.bits
        Reconstructed frames    sony-ct1.decoded
        Decoding trace          sony-ct1.trace ( Picture Layer Level)

	Bit rate:               2 Mbit/sec 
	Sampling dimensions:    352 x 224  24 Hz 
	Number of frames:	60 frames
	IDCT:                   double precision


        
        *frame format:

	4:2:0 frame ("display" order) 8 bit

	              width              
                +---------------+       
                |               |          
                |      Y0       | height
                |               |
                |  width/2      |
                +-------+-------+
                |  Cb0  | 
                |       |height/2
                +-------+
                |  Cr0  |height/2
                |       |
                +-------+-------+        
                |               |
                |      Y1       |
                |               |        
                |               |        
                +-------+-------+ 
                |       |



Please check that you can decode it.  Thank-you.

        Best regards,

        Motoki Kato,
	Katsumi Tahara

